nodes.text: The Sabetue were a species of tall, gaunt, and skeletal sentients with claws on their hands and feet. The color of their skin indicated their gender or lack thereof; notably, those with pure white skin were genderless.

In 13 BBY on Corellia, a genderless Sabetue individual and a male being named Kilmo met with one of Lady Proxima's White Worms, a human named Han Solo, with the intent of purchasing seven vials of coaxium. Realizing Solo was withholding some of the agreed-upon vials, the Sabetue attempted to grab the White Worm before a pursuit ensued.
